# Add Waybar icon when installing UI applications

When adding a new GUI application to the NixOS config (e.g. to `home.packages` or `environment.systemPackages`), also add a matching Nerd Font icon entry to the `window-rewrite` map in:

`modules/desktop/hyprland/programs/waybar/default.nix`

The entry maps the application's Hyprland window class to a Nerd Font icon, e.g.:

```nix
"obsidian" = "󱓧";
```

Use an icon that visually represents the application's purpose (e.g. a globe for browsers, a note for note apps, a gamepad for game launchers). Browse https://www.nerdfonts.com/cheat-sheet for icons.

This does **not** apply to CLI-only tools or background services — only applications that open a visible window.
